        <abstract> 
<p>M. J. Berkeley wrote <hi rend="italic">London Review &amp; Wkly J. Polit.</hi> article.</p> 
            <p>CD is "out of sight the best physiological observer and experimenter that Botany ever saw".</p> 
<p>Laments how much he [JDH] missed when doing the <hi rend="italic">Listera</hi> ["Functions and structure of the rostellum of <hi rend="italic">Listera ovata</hi>", <hi rend="italic">Philos. Trans. R. Soc. Lond.</hi> 144 (1854): 259–64].</p> 
            <p>Illness of wife and father.</p>
            <p>"More plants from Fernando Po and more European".</p>
